<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99633312440571></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99633312440571><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99633312440571>RE: spell book</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99633312440571#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=22327><span id= >Nolewen</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>6 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Jul 28th 11:12 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I see so many people these days asking how to organize spell books! And Badjur's right: it has more to do with the player than the game. But no one seems to mention this method, yet I find it useful:<br><br>Place all of your "hot swap" spells -- usually buffs -- on the first pages. For example, you don't often have Cure Poison up, but you might want it handy and not have to go turning page after page looking for it.&nbsp;&nbsp;Even hotkeying "/book 17" requires you to look for the hotkey while the poison is eating away at your victim. Putting it on the first page usually allows you drop, mem, stand and cast quickly.<br><br>Place your "standard line-up" of spells on pages 3 & 4.  Or somewhere farther back and hotkey it. Basically what I go for here is when I die, all the spells I'm going to re-mem are on the same page/screen. Also, having them handy is a follow-up to the first tip. Now that you've cast your buff/cure, you'll want to put the old spell back.<br><br>For me, after these two setups, it's prety much pot-luck, although I tend to try and group similar spells together (poisons, debuffs, buffs, etc).<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

