	   <tr><td colspan=2>Rofl, I have heard it enough, "shamans can't solo, Shamans can't melee, Shamans can't do this and that" Let me tell you what Bs that is. I currenly have a 52 Ogre Shaman on Rodcet Nife and let me tell you that Shamans are one of he best classes to solo with. Lol can't melee? who says? My Ogre shaman can pack more punch in a hit than any hybrid class. You have the greatest melee ability out of the priest classes, make that into good use. My Ogre shaman hits for around 160 a hit.. I believe they are the best class in the game, they can melee, they have very cool magiks, etc. They have a hard life indeed but at the end they are the best class!<br><br>Solo techniques: <br>1. Buff your abilities, Talismen spells work like a charm.<br><br>2. Root the target.<br><br>3. Cast a DoT spell on him to quickly rain out his life.<br><br>4. Blast him 3 times with a DD. <br><br>5. By now you will problably have un out of mana or have very little left, the monster will be dead my now or have very little Hp left on him<br><br>6 Engage in melee combat to finish him off. I personally don't Nuke since shammies nukes aren't the greatest, Instead I melee much more than other shamans do. it all depends on the class you choose.<br><br>_________________________________________________<br><br>Play your role right in a group<br><br>You will rarely be called on as the group healer thanks to clerics, or druid (Since druids have more mana than you.) Your job in the group is to buff everyone up with the talisman line of spells or regular buffs depending on your level. We shamans aren't in high demand in groups. So it can be quite difficult to find one.<br>Also if the party is fighting a black or yellow or even red, cast your DoT, don't waste your mana casting a Dot on a blue mob..<br><br>I have learned from he best and&nbsp;&nbsp;hope you learned a little from me :)<br><br><br>Phattey Chubz<br>Level 52 Ogre Shaman<br>Rodcet Nife<br>Peace :p<br><br