<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99555005671862></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99555005671862><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99555005671862>RE: thinking of making a Shaman</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99555005671862#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=34142><span id=Scholar>Shjekai</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>67 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jul 19th 9:40 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.95]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As with any class pick a race you like. As you play you will be able to overcome the obsticles of whatever you choose. Shaman are not melee. You can do a little damage but from about 20, or even earlier, your mana is what makes you valuable. Even the best twinked shaman can't compare to a warrior duel wielding, double attacking and kicking. You are best served by buffing that warrior (or monk or ranger, etc) and medding for heals, haste or what have you. Melee while soloing is only useful to kill a fleeing mob or at low levels. Once you get Cannibalize those hps you are losing in a fight equate to lost mana you could be getting after, or even during, the fight from converted hps. Melee for fun but don't get used to it. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
