	   <tr><td colspan=2>I went to Lake of Ill Omen when I was 15th level.&nbsp;&nbsp;I'm now 21st level and I'm still getting good exp there, not to mention the loot brings in some good money.  I can make about 15pp a night as long as I don't get into a group with a bunch of loot mongers.  Shamans are always welcome in groups in LoIO.  I will warn you, you are most likely going to be your groups main healer so you will spend most of your time on your butt with your face in your book.  The other nice thing about it is there are lots of Enchanters who are more than willing to trade Breeze or Clarity for SoW.  I suggest keeping to the "Mill" area until you are a bit higher in level.  You didn't say what race you are so if you are not a Barbarian, you need to know that you will be KOS is Firiona Vie which is the connecting zone that I go through.  Good luck to you in where you decide to hunt.<br>&nbsp;<br>Being polite will get you more than being rude.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>Windlore MacImashee<br>&lt;Alliance Of Steel&gt; </td></tr>
